<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1545,1933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">
Diagnosis: This species has been described adequately by 
<bibRefCitation author="Drew, R. A. I. &amp; Hancock, D. L. &amp; White, I. M." box="[860,1070,1582,1609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" pagination="567 - 654" refId="ref5925" refString="Drew, R. A. I., Hancock, D. L. &amp; White, I. M. (1998) Revision of the tropical fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae: Dacinae) of South East Asia, II. Dacus Fabricius. Invertebrate Taxonomy, 12, 567 - 654. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IT 96004" type="journal article" year="1998">
Drew 
<emphasis box="[930,980,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">et al</emphasis>
. (1998)
</bibRefCitation>
except for postabdominal structures. It is a predominantly black species with a largely black face (red-brown centrally), broad costal band confluent with 
<collectionCode box="[247,266,1655,1681]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">R</collectionCode>
<subScript attach="left" box="[266,292,1672,1686]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">4+5</subScript>
and expanded apically, fore and mid femora wholly black, hind femur 0.6 black; abdomen with reddish brown areas submedially on tergites IV-V (extending marginally onto tergite III in the present specimen) separated by a black medial vitta. Epandrium heavily sclerotised, black. Lateral surstylus shorter than epandrium; posterior lobe of surstylus 6−7 times longer than anterior lobe. Epandrium and surstyli bulb-shaped in posterior view; medial surstylus shorter than lateral surstylus and with black, finger-like prensisetae. Phallus elongate (
<quantity box="[1264,1369,1798,1825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.28" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" unit="mm" value="2.28">2.28 mm</quantity>
) with sclerotised glans (
<quantity box="[352,457,1833,1861]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.699999999999999" pageId="5" pageNumber="558" unit="mm" value="0.57">0.57 mm</quantity>
); acrophallus with single patterned tubule, preglans lobe and subapical lobe present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1545,1933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">
Remarks: Described from central 
<collectingCountry box="[586,688,1870,1896]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, this species is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[1237,1298,1870,1896]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="558">India</collectingCountry>
. It has been collected in Zingerone traps.
</paragraph>
